# Code Review Checklist

## Correctness

- [ ] Logic is correct and handles edge cases
- [ ] No off-by-one errors or boundary issues
- [ ] Error states are handled properly
- [ ] Async operations handle race conditions

## Conventions

- [ ] Follows project naming conventions
- [ ] Matches existing code style and patterns
- [ ] Uses established abstractions (no reinventing)
- [ ] Types are properly defined (no `any` abuse)

## Security

- [ ] User input is validated/sanitized
- [ ] No sensitive data in logs or responses
- [ ] Authentication/authorization checked where needed
- [ ] No SQL injection, XSS, or CSRF vulnerabilities

## Performance

- [ ] No unnecessary re-renders (React)
- [ ] No N+1 queries or excessive API calls
- [ ] Large lists use virtualization if needed
- [ ] Expensive computations are memoized

## Maintainability

- [ ] Code is self-documenting (clear names)
- [ ] Complex logic has comments explaining "why"
- [ ] No dead code or unused imports
- [ ] Single responsibility principle followed

## Testing

- [ ] Critical paths have test coverage
- [ ] Edge cases are tested
- [ ] Tests are deterministic (no flaky tests)

## Output Format

```markdown
## Review Summary

**Approval**: ✅ Approved / ⚠️ Needs Changes / ❌ Rejected

### Issues Found
- [severity] file:line - description

### Suggestions
- [optional] improvement ideas
```
